These are really nice and yes 100% authentic.  Some of the ones without any visible wrinkles/creases would probably grade an SGC 50 or 60 and would be worth the effort to get them graded at an $8 - $10 grading fee rate (50s go for $40ish and 60s go for $80ish).  The ones with creases are worth between $15-$25, generally, and are not worth the fees, obviously.  

Again, great cards!  Thanks for sharing!
